    "body": "New references: \r\n\r\nThe error decoding is here:\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/eth2_libp2p/src/rpc/codec/ssz_snappy.rs#L405\r\n\r\nThe Error type we want is here: \r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/eth2_libp2p/src/rpc/methods.rs#L22\r\n\r\nCurrently this is decoding a string, sending it to the BaseOutboundCodec which then converts the string into the error type. It would be nicer to have the BaseOutboundCodec return the error type directly and check the length before decoding into a string. \r\n\r\nI.e I think we should just use the logic in the From impl here: https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/master/beacon_node/eth2_libp2p/src/rpc/methods.rs#L24\r\ndirectly in the decoding after checking the length and returning the ErrorType directly. \r\n\r\n",
